radiographic_examinations.findings: Fluid-filled structure in the right lower quadrant medial to the cecum measuring 10-14 mm in diameter, with hyperenhancement of the wall and surrounding fat stranding and reactive free fluid. No evidence of obstruction or wall edema. The bladder, prostate, and rectum appear unremarkable. Calcified atherosclerotic disease in the distal aortoiliac and femoral branches. Degenerative disc disease and degenerative joint disease present in the lumbosacral spine.
